name: Microservice
description: In this project, I have implemented the basic logics for developing microservices-oriented web service applications. In addition to three providers, there are also applications dedicated to Health Check and Gateway functionalities.

name: kubernetes-manifest-files-for-11-tier-microservices-application
description: This repo contains kube manifest files and docker containers of microservices gotten from google.

name: ecommerce-api
description: This project includes an e-commerce microservices application created using Node.js, Express, MongoDB, Docker, and Nginx. Microservices architecture divides your application into small, independent services, making development and scalability easier. In this project, fundamental e-commerce functionalities will be implemented.

name: Petclinic-Microservices-With-Db
description: This project aims to create full CI/CD Pipeline for microservice based applications using [Spring Petclinic Microservices Application](https://github.com/spring-petclinic/spring-petclinic-microservices). Jenkins Server deployed on Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2) Instance is used as CI/CD Server to build pipelines.

name: docker-services-demo
description: A demo of a primitive, Docker container, microservices application.

name: tiergesund-webapp
description: A distributed microservices web application based on Spring Cloud

name: fastApi_OnlineRecipeSystem
description: Application Name: Online Recipe System using fastApi and microservice approach

name: mb-redirector
description: Microservice for redirecting clients to their applications based on their emails

name: Microservice-Project-Spring2020
description: ASRC Federal Mission Solutions is in the process of evaluating some of our larger programs for decomposition into microservices. The team will start with a single, monolithic application of their choosing and decompose it into a group of microservices that provide the same functionality.  The solution will leverage Docker Containers for the runtime environment. The teams experience and recommendations will provide valuable insights for AFMS into software decomposition process.

name: springboot-react-ecommerce-app
description: eCommerce application based on the microservices architecture built using Spring Boot and ReactJS.

name: Microshopproject
description: A small back-end for a shopping application. Supports three microservices, using Maven multi-module file structure. Technologies used: [Java, Spring Boot, Maven Multi-Modules, MySQL, Microservice, REST API]

name: node-typescript-auth-keys-generator
description: Node | Express | TypeScript | API/REST microservice that generates API keys and secret keys to sign JWT tokens, according to parameters specified by client applications.

name: QRC-BASED-FINANCIAL-APP---BACKEND
description: Welcome to the backend repository of our QR code-based financial transaction application. We are currently in the development phase, working hard to create a groundbreaking solution that will revolutionize financial transactions. Our mission is to make transactions fast and seamless using a microservices-based architecture.
